\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Motivating example from JSONSchemaBench medium instance \texttt  {o9875} (API route config). The schema requires \texttt  {method}$\,\in \,$\texttt  {["get","post","put",\ldots  ]} (lowercase enum) and each \texttt  {experienceGroupIds} item to match \texttt  {\^{}[A-Fa-f0-9]\{24\}\$} (24-character hex, e.g.\ MongoDB ObjectId). \textbf  {(1)}~The diffusion model's batch unmask produces \texttt  {"GET"} (fails lowercase enum, position $c$) and \texttt  {"grp\_abc"} (fails 24-char hex pattern, position $s{-}1$); the violated span covers both. \textbf  {(2a)}~\textbf  {LAVE} samples $K$ random completions from $c$: satisfying both the enum \emph  {and} the exact-24 hex pattern simultaneously requires $P\!\approx \!(16/|V|)^{24}\!\approx \!0$, no valid completion is ever drawn; LAVE times out at 120\,s (255+ mean draws overall). \textbf  {(2b)}~\textbf  {Dgrammar} forces \texttt  {"get"} at $c$ via \texttt  {LLMatcher} masking (enum fixed), but the hex-pattern violation at $s{-}1$ requires 100 resamples to generate a valid 24-character string (84.9\% overall validity). \textbf  {(2c)}~\textbf  {DPGrammar} runs Viterbi over $[c,s)$ jointly, assigning both \texttt  {"get"} and a valid 24-char hex ID in one pass, only 7 resamples on this instance (99.2\% overall validity).}}{2}{figure.caption.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:motivating}{{1}{2}{Motivating example from JSONSchemaBench medium instance \texttt {o9875} (API route config). The schema requires \texttt {method}$\,\in \,$\texttt {["get","post","put",\ldots ]} (lowercase enum) and each \texttt {experienceGroupIds} item to match \texttt {\^{}[A-Fa-f0-9]\{24\}\$} (24-character hex, e.g.\ MongoDB ObjectId). \textbf {(1)}~The diffusion model's batch unmask produces \texttt {"GET"} (fails lowercase enum, position $c$) and \texttt {"grp\_abc"} (fails 24-char hex pattern, position $s{-}1$); the violated span covers both. \textbf {(2a)}~\textbf {LAVE} samples $K$ random completions from $c$: satisfying both the enum \emph {and} the exact-24 hex pattern simultaneously requires $P\!\approx \!(16/|V|)^{24}\!\approx \!0$, no valid completion is ever drawn; LAVE times out at 120\,s (255+ mean draws overall). \textbf {(2b)}~\textbf {Dgrammar} forces \texttt {"get"} at $c$ via \texttt {LLMatcher} masking (enum fixed), but the hex-pattern violation at $s{-}1$ requires 100 resamples to generate a valid 24-character string (84.9\% overall validity). \textbf {(2c)}~\textbf {DPGrammar} runs Viterbi over $[c,s)$ jointly, assigning both \texttt {"get"} and a valid 24-char hex ID in one pass, only 7 resamples on this instance (99.2\% overall validity)}{figure.caption.1}{}}
